.row-fluid
  .span12
    %h2
      Searchable Map Template 
      %small with Google Fusion Tables
    %h4 Turn a spreadsheet in to a searchable map
    %p You want to put your data on a searchable, filterable map. This is a free, open source tool to help you do it.
    %hr
.row-fluid
  .span6
    %h4 Features
    %ul
      %li clean, full screen layout
      %li
        %strong new
        mobile and tablet friendly using responsive design
      %li address search (with variable radius)
      %li geolocation (find me!)
      %li
        %strong new
        RESTful URLs for sharing searches
      %li results count (using Google's Fusion Tables API)
      %li ability to easily add additional search filters (checkboxes, sliders, etc)
      %li all done with HTML, CSS and Javascript - no server side code required

  .span6
    %h4 Technologies used
    %ul
      %li
        %a{:href => "http://www.google.com/fusiontables"} Google Fusion Tables
        (
        %a{:href => "https://github.com/derekeder/FusionTable-Map-Template#resources"}> useful resources
        )
      %li
        %a{:href => "http://code.google.com/apis/maps/documentation/javascript/"} Google Maps API V3
      %li
        %a{:href => "http://jquery.com"} jQuery
      %li
        %a{:href => "http://www.asual.com/jquery/address"} jQuery Address
      %li
        %a{:href => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap"} Twitter Bootstrap
    %p
      %strong Note:
      This template is now supports the
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "https://developers.google.com/fusiontables/docs/v1/using"} Fusion Tables v1 API
      For more info on this, see their
      %a{:href => "https://developers.google.com/fusiontables/docs/v1/migration_guide"} migration guide

